This paper deals with the problem of attributing the prediction of a deep network to its input features, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a new attribution method called Integrated Gradients and applies it to various models in different domains such as image, text, and chemistry. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
